sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1486014
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part has a fused protein downstream of an arabinose-inducible promoter: IFP[1]-CpxR. Biobrick BBa_K1486015 has IFP[2]-CpxR with an arabinose promoter. This construct was made in both orientations: BBa_K1486012 is CpxR-IFP[1] (with an arabinose promoter).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Both orientations were made, as well as for IFP[2] so all dimerizations could be tested (see main page for biobrick numbers). Flexible linkers were used to fuse both proteins, and an RBS was put between the promoter and the cds.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGem EPFL 2014

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1486000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The part has been extracted from the E coli genome.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: CpxR is a transciption factor that dimerizes and becomes active when phosphorylated by the transmembrane histidine kinase CpxA. CpxA in turn becomes active when the bacterial cell is submitted to different kinds of shock (pH, temperature, pressure, protein misfolding in the inter-membrane space...).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: When making composite parts with CpxR that are supposed to dimerize, we had to take care about the positioning of the other elements regarding the parallel dimerization of CpxR.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGem EPFL 2014

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1486004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Flexible linker used to fuse two proteins.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Designed considering the flexibility and separation needed between our fused proteins.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGem EPFL 2014

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1486006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the first part of the split infrared fluorescent protein (IFP1.4). To be used with IFP[2].
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: When fused to another coding sequence, insert a flexible linker
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGem EPFL 2014
